fields.physical_description: Album of designs (164) mounted on 118 sheets of white wove paper, half-bound and containing the book-plates of Charles Edward Fewster, Hull, c.1861-8.Including ceramic designs for Minton, wallpaper designs for William Woollam and William Cooke, chairs (2) in the Egyptian style, designs for jugs and ewers, and Celtic and Arabic ornament. Also metalwork "Designed by Welby Pugin" and (p.113) a design for atrade card for Thos. Fewster & Sons Manufacturers of Varnishes and Patent Dryers.Several sheets signed in ink C.D.
fields.title: Album of designs; 2 Albums
fields.materials_techniques: Pencil, ink, watercolour and bodycolour on tracing paper
